	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I figured out a method of displaying NES graphics by compositing with an NES emulator in the front and a cartoon in the back. Essentially what I'm doing is color key based on the color in $3F00. This could be used to implement a transparent emulator:<br /><ul><li>One person wants to play games while someone else wants to do something else </li><li>Graphical facelifts that watch the game state and insert appropriate backgrounds </li></ul><br /><a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/overlay/rocktv.webm" class="postlink"><img src="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/overlay/rocktv_01_40_00.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />Watch</a><br /><br />(To play WebM video, use VLC Media Player, Firefox, Chrome, or Opera, or install the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/webmmf/" class="postlink">WebM plug-in for IE 9</a>.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
